Attributing Sin to Prophets: The Quranic narratives often differ from the Hebrew Bible by absolving prophets like Lot and David from sins attributed to them in biblical accounts, thereby restoring what is seen as their true, infallible nature [52][26][49] .
The Exploit - Veneration of Ezra: The Quran makes a specific and controversial claim in Surah 9:30: "The Jews say, 'Ezra is the son of Allah'" [37][38][54][55][48] . While mainstream Judaism does not hold this belief, Islamic exegetes have offered several interpretations [39][55][56] :
